    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Senior Financial Analyst to strengthen our Vadodara-based team.\n\nAbout Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners:\nBajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in VBA\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vadodara, Gujarat, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Bajaj Allianz Life South Asia Partners!",
